Source: WHO Disease Outbreaks Report, Wed 25 Oct 2000 [edited

Rift Valley Fever in Saudi Arabia - WHO Update 3
------------------------------------------------
As of Tue 23 Oct 2000, 443 cases of Rift Valley fever with 85 deaths were
reported by the Ministry of Health of Saudi Arabia. [Previously on 19 Oct
2000, the Ministry of Health had reported 413 cases and 83 deaths.
There appears to be a declining trend in the rate of occurrence of cases and
deaths. All cases occurred in Jizan and Asir provinces and the disease has
not spread to the northwest area of the country.
A joint technical team has been formed by the Ministries of Health and
Agriculture of Saudi Arabia and Yemen to control the outbreak. For further
details, please see the Saudi Arabia Information Resource web site.
